HEADWORD: Fallibility
<hw>Fal`li*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of
being fallible; liability to deceive or to be deceived; <as>as, the
<ex>fallibity</ex> of an argument or of an adviser</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

